arious stages in his career. Because each contributor concentrates on the Douglas Duncan he knew the result is a personal, vivid and immediate portrait of a very attractive man. The book also includes reproductions of paintings by some of the artists whose work Duncan encouraged and collected, and examples of his work as a bookbinder and a photographer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Artists, Architects, Photographers.2bisacsh1 aClark, Paraskeva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEndicott, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinch, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrye, Northrop, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayden, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Alan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKettle, Rik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoon, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOgilvie, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearson, Lester B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWayne, Johnny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148759994240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487599942423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487599942.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACK